•
TIP 1: Make the stair master your best friend!
TIP 2: change your lifestyle, don’t call it a diet. I personally enjoy how I eat now! Finding new healthy foods and drink! 
TIP 3: When you “cheat” you’re only cheating yourself and your results! STAY DISCIPLINED.. 💪🏽💙
TIP 4: Have someone help you stay motivated (gym buddy) I’m forever grateful for @rjxevans recording our progress kept me motivated!! 💪🏽💪🏽 and @kvn2taj keeping me motivated on those stairs!!

Mental Health is a very real thing that can go unnoticed,  or even ignored and I can honestly say I used to be one of those people… Starting with the youth, it is extremely important we implement any and every program in schools to make sure these kids don’t go unseen or unheard. THEY ARE THE FUTURE. Unfortunately with recent episodes in my life I’ve come to realize it is a harsh reality people face on a day to day basis.  From here on out I will use my platform to make sure people know they have someone to talk to at all times. As a father of two I will be the role model for them to continue on being there for their peers as they grow up 💙. #HelpUsHelpThemPA #sponsored
